I forgot the way to the office?

257
00:18:27.733 --> 00:18:28.900
The meeting's changed.

258
00:18:28.901 --> 00:18:30.528
We're going to Pasadena now.

259
00:18:30.611 --> 00:18:32.238
We are?
Fine. we can take my truck.

260
00:18:32.321 --> 00:18:34.949
We could if the plan was to make
the world's worst impression.

261
00:18:35.032 --> 00:18:37.326
Oh. I don't have to plan for that.
That happens naturally.

262
00:18:37.410 --> 00:18:40.121
I'll say. you were just four
words from contempt of court.

263
00:18:40.204 --> 00:18:42.039
Go fuck yourself.
I could have got that in.

264
00:18:42.123 --> 00:18:44.375
Thus demonstrating
your masterful knowledge

265
00:18:44.458 --> 00:18:46.458
- of legal decorum.
- Frank Dillon is sitting there

266
00:18:46.502 --> 00:18:48.796
like a monument to the useless
and the judge is concerned

267
00:18:48.879 --> 00:18:51.424
with my decorum?
Why didn't he hold him in contempt?

268
00:18:51.507 --> 00:18:53.134
Because I sure as hell did.

269
00:18:53.217 --> 00:18:54.719
Letting him dig into me
like that.

270
00:18:54.802 --> 00:18:56.636
A fucking peanut vendor
would have known to object.

271
00:18:56.637 --> 00:18:59.015
So many windmills. so little time.

272
00:19:02.977 --> 00:19:04.353
How are you today. Miss Street?

273
00:19:05.688 --> 00:19:06.772
Peachy.

274
00:19:06.856 --> 00:19:08.649
How are you. Mr. Mason?

275
00:19:10.818 --> 00:19:12.527
I wasn't expecting
a congregation.

276
00:19:12.528 --> 00:19:14.739
I rely on Miss Street

277
00:19:14.822 --> 00:19:16.490
to keep the facts straight.
Herman.

278
00:19:16.574 --> 00:19:18.451
Do you intend
to take notes. miss?

279
00:19:18.534 --> 00:19:20.286
That's generally what I do.

280
00:19:20.369 --> 00:19:22.038
Unless you object.

281
00:19:23.039 --> 00:19:25.207
And you're a detective.
Mr. Mason?

282
00:19:25.291 --> 00:19:27.918
It's a fancy word
for a busybody. but yes.

283
00:19:28.002 --> 00:19:31.839
We've been working together
since... when was it?

284
00:19:31.922 --> 00:19:33.507
Just after the war.

285
00:19:33.591 --> 00:19:36.010
Gave him his first job back
from France.

286
00:19:36.093 --> 00:19:38.471
- isn't that right. Perry?
- You served overseas?

287
00:19:38.554 --> 00:19:39.889
With lots of other farm boys.

288
00:19:39.972 --> 00:19:41.724
Mr. Mason was in the army.

289
00:19:41.807 --> 00:19:44.894
survived the Battle of the Argonne.

290
00:19:44.977 --> 00:19:47.605
How can we help you. Mr. Baggerly?

291
00:19:47.688 --> 00:19:50.441
It's not me that needs help. Mr. Mason.

292
00:19:50.524 --> 00:19:53.194
Matthew and Emily Dodson.

293
00:19:53.986 --> 00:19:56.364
an unspeakable act...

294
00:19:56.447 --> 00:19:58.783
was visited upon them.
they're quite overwhelmed.

295
00:19:58.866 --> 00:20:00.826
Consider us
at their service.

296
00:20:02.411 --> 00:20:03.411
Friends of yours?

297
00:20:04.330 --> 00:20:05.664
Members of my church.

298
00:20:06.457 --> 00:20:08.918
Working people without many resources.

299
00:20:09.043 --> 00:20:12.213
Well. God has put you
in their path.

300
00:20:12.922 --> 00:20:14.673
Is this a...

301
00:20:14.757 --> 00:20:16.384
Radiant Assembly of God.

302
00:20:16.467 --> 00:20:17.968
Right. On the radio.

303
00:20:18.052 --> 00:20:19.095
Sister Alice.

304
00:20:19.845 --> 00:20:22.556
A woman of wonder-working power.

305
00:20:22.640 --> 00:20:25.851
I won't hesitate to say
that she changed my life.

306
00:20:25.935 --> 00:20:30.106
Do the Dodsons know
you contacted me. Herman?

307
00:20:30.189 --> 00:20:33.317
They're anxiously
awaiting your guidance. Elias.

308
00:20:33.401 --> 00:20:34.610
What about the police?

309
00:20:36.237 --> 00:20:37.488
How's that?

310
00:20:37.571 --> 00:20:39.407
Well. they'll be
on this hammer and tongs.

311
00:20:39.490 --> 00:20:40.658
Why not leave it to them?

312
00:20:45.538 --> 00:20:46.997
I'll be frank. Mr. Mason.

313
00:20:49.291 --> 00:20:51.919
I don't trust the Los Angeles
Police Department

314
00:20:52.002 --> 00:20:53.421
to do the job that's needed.

315
00:20:56.257 --> 00:20:57.550
Neither would I.

316
00:21:09.395 --> 00:21:10.875
So you found this upstairs?

317
00:21:10.938 --> 00:21:12.606
I told you. my wife did.

318
00:21:12.690 --> 00:21:14.442
- I was at work.
- And she called you?

319
00:21:15.276 --> 00:21:17.278
Yeah. Hysterical.

320
00:21:17.361 --> 00:21:19.071
Why'd neither one of you
call the police?

321
00:21:19.822 --> 00:21:20.865
Read the note.

322
00:21:21.699 --> 00:21:22.950
You can read. can't you?

323
00:21:24.493 --> 00:21:26.454
So your wife finds the note.

324
00:21:26.537 --> 00:21:28.164
calls you. what she do next?

325
00:21:28.247 --> 00:21:29.727
How should I know? Ask her.

326
00:21:29.748 --> 00:21:31.228
We'll get to her in a minute.

327
00:21:31.292 --> 00:21:33.085
You own a grocery store.

328
00:21:33.169 --> 00:21:34.253
much money in that?

329
00:21:34.712 --> 00:21:35.670
What?

330
00:21:35.671 --> 00:21:38.340
Nice house for a grocer.
It can't be cheap to maintain.

331
00:21:39.467 --> 00:21:40.884
- What's that supposed to mean?
- How long does it take to get

332
00:21:40.885 --> 00:21:43.470
- from the grocery store to here?
- What difference does it make?

333
00:21:43.471 --> 00:21:45.138
- Easy. Matthew.
- How... Are you suggesting

334
00:21:45.139 --> 00:21:46.682
I had something to do with it?

335
00:21:47.141 --> 00:21:50.102
- What the hell?
- Just covering all angles. Mr. Dodson.

336
00:21:50.186 --> 00:21:52.605
Where was I? Who saw me?
I didn't kidnap my son.

337
00:21:52.688 --> 00:21:54.314
- I didn't murder my own son.
- No one is saying

338
00:21:54.315 --> 00:21:55.858
- you did.
- Well. he is!

339
00:21:56.442 --> 00:21:58.777
He's dancing around.
but that's what he fucking thinks.

340
00:21:58.861 --> 00:22:01.261
Maybe this is
a good time for a little break.

341
00:22:01.280 --> 00:22:03.407
Sound okay to you.
Detective Holcomb?

342
00:22:06.202 --> 00:22:07.244
Yeah. Why not?

343
00:22:07.828 --> 00:22:09.163
Get some fresh air.

344
00:22:09.246 --> 00:22:11.331
It's all right. You treated me
like... you can't...

345
00:22:11.332 --> 00:22:13.124
- you can't just walk...
- Easy now. Matthew.

346
00:22:13.125 --> 00:22:15.461
Let's have a little drink
of cold water. shall we?

347
00:22:16.504 --> 00:22:19.173
Water. Right. great idea.
That'll fix everything.

348
00:22:19.256 --> 00:22:21.175
This is all part
of the process.

349
00:22:21.300 --> 00:22:24.303
Are you kidding?
Look out there. it's a goddamn zoo.

350
00:24:17.124 --> 00:24:19.335
Are you the man that
works with Mr. Jonathan?

351
00:24:22.212 --> 00:24:23.922
Yes. ma'am.

352
00:24:24.256 --> 00:24:25.466
Perry.

353
00:24:29.720 --> 00:24:31.055
I'm Emily Dodson.

354
00:24:32.014 --> 00:24:33.140
Charlie's mother.

355
00:24:40.314 --> 00:24:42.191
Offer you a cigarette. Mrs. Dodson?

356
00:24:44.610 --> 00:24:46.362
If you promise not to tell
my husband.

357
00:24:48.197 --> 00:24:49.365
Wouldn't dream of it.

358
00:25:07.841 --> 00:25:08.842
Thank you.

359
00:25:13.263 --> 00:25:15.182
You were in the war.
weren't you?

360
00:25:17.643 --> 00:25:19.645
The way you hold your cigarette.

361
00:25:19.728 --> 00:25:21.230
Hiding the ember in your palm.

362
00:25:22.356 --> 00:25:24.942
I guess I'm still trained not to give
them something to shoot at.

363
00:25:26.694 --> 00:25:28.612
Was your husband over there?

364
00:25:30.781 --> 00:25:31.782
Brother.

365
00:25:32.950 --> 00:25:35.828
I haven't seen him
since we left Missouri.

366
00:25:35.911 --> 00:25:38.163
I really wish they'd let me
clean in here.

367
00:25:40.457 --> 00:25:41.917
All this fingerprint dust...

368
00:25:43.794 --> 00:25:45.546
Can't help feeling that it...

369
00:25:45.629 --> 00:25:47.423
reflects poorly on me somehow.

370
00:25:48.632 --> 00:25:50.926
Oh. I don't think poorly of you.

371
00:25:53.387 --> 00:25:54.388
God does.

372
00:25:56.473 --> 00:25:57.766
That's why I'm being punished.

373
00:26:02.855 --> 00:26:05.482
Do you have children. Mr. Perry?

374
00:26:05.566 --> 00:26:08.444
It's Mason. Perry is my first name.

375
00:26:09.695 --> 00:26:10.779
I have a son.

376
00:26:12.656 --> 00:26:13.991
What's his name?

377
00:26:17.286 --> 00:26:18.412
Theodore.

378
00:26:18.495 --> 00:26:19.538
Teddy.

379
00:26:21.582 --> 00:26:23.083
How old?

380
00:26:23.167 --> 00:26:24.710
Nine in February.

381
00:26:28.881 --> 00:26:30.132
Charlie likes turtles.

382
00:26:32.760 --> 00:26:33.844
Liked.

383
00:26:38.056 --> 00:26:39.516
What's your boy fond of?

384
00:26:43.729 --> 00:26:44.772
Firetrucks.

385
00:26:49.985 --> 00:26:51.236
I bet.

386
00:26:52.946 --> 00:26:55.824
Nine is a good age for a boy.

387
00:27:08.170 --> 00:27:09.338
So...

388
00:27:11.965 --> 00:27:13.175
I'm sorry.

389
00:27:23.268 --> 00:27:24.668
Yeah. fine. he's a hothead.

390
00:27:24.686 --> 00:27:26.563
but he's a little too touchy
if you ask me.

391
00:27:27.356 --> 00:27:28.774
And her?

392
00:27:28.857 --> 00:27:31.568
She was just sitting
downstairs the whole time?

393
00:27:31.652 --> 00:27:34.238
She told the detectives
she gave the boy a bath.

394
00:27:34.321 --> 00:27:35.531
put him to bed.

395
00:27:35.614 --> 00:27:38.784
fell asleep by the fire
listening to the radio.

396
00:27:38.867 --> 00:27:41.119
Actually.
she puts Charlie to bed.

397
00:27:41.203 --> 00:27:43.163
goes downstairs
to clean up the kitchen.

398
00:27:43.247 --> 00:27:45.123
goes back upstairs
to check on him

399
00:27:45.207 --> 00:27:47.042
then goes downstairs
and falls asleep

400
00:27:47.125 --> 00:27:48.377
listening to the radio.

401
00:27:49.503 --> 00:27:51.505
She doesn't twitch an eyelid

402
00:27:51.588 --> 00:27:55.342
while someone creeps into her house
and nabs her kid?

403
00:27:55.425 --> 00:27:58.178
- You think she's a drinker?
- No. She's a mother.

404
00:27:58.929 --> 00:28:01.682
Feeding. changing.
burping. screaming.

405
00:28:01.765 --> 00:28:03.141
you wouldn't last a minute.

406
00:28:03.225 --> 00:28:04.825
Is this something
you know about?

407
00:28:05.644 --> 00:28:07.479
Call it an educated guess.

408
00:28:12.359 --> 00:28:14.319
All right. You're the kidnapper.

409
00:28:14.403 --> 00:28:16.446
you have to case that house
long enough to know

410
00:28:16.530 --> 00:28:18.240
Matthew's hours
at the grocery store.

411
00:28:18.323 --> 00:28:20.576
the time Emily
gives Charlie the bath.

412
00:28:20.659 --> 00:28:21.659
then puts him down.

413
00:28:21.910 --> 00:28:23.287
then falls asleep herself.

414
00:28:23.370 --> 00:28:24.997
Unless you have someone on the inside.

415
00:28:25.080 --> 00:28:27.249
Oh. so you agree with the police.

416
00:28:27.332 --> 00:28:29.877
You think the Dodsons
had something to do with it.

417
00:28:29.960 --> 00:28:32.629
- I'm not agreeing with anyone.
- I sure hope not.

418
00:28:32.713 --> 00:28:33.922
I've stood with those two.

419
00:28:34.590 --> 00:28:36.967
That's grief. not guilt.

420
00:28:37.301 --> 00:28:38.927
I'm just pointing out that someone knew

421
00:28:39.011 --> 00:28:40.804
they were good for a hundred grand.

422
00:28:40.888 --> 00:28:42.389
How do you figure that from a guy

423
00:28:42.472 --> 00:28:45.517
who sells pickled cucumbers
and aftershaves?

424
00:28:45.601 --> 00:28:47.102
It's queer from both sides.

425
00:28:47.185 --> 00:28:48.478
And the baby.

426
00:28:49.771 --> 00:28:53.150
Someone stood over Charlie
and stitched those eyes.

427
00:28:56.695 --> 00:28:58.363
Yeah. it's a dark tone.

428
00:28:58.447 --> 00:29:00.824
long. long. deep. dark tone.

429
00:29:04.661 --> 00:29:06.580
Wipe it off. gentles.

430
00:29:06.663 --> 00:29:08.290
We do what we're asked to do.

431
00:29:08.373 --> 00:29:10.709
Well. that's easy for you to say.

432
00:29:10.792 --> 00:29:12.960
Detectives aren't gonna like me
over their shoulder on this.

433
00:29:12.961 --> 00:29:14.420
And I got a license
that could get pulled.

434
00:29:14.421 --> 00:29:15.713
So you don't want the job?

435
00:29:15.714 --> 00:29:17.758
Did I say that?

436
00:29:18.216 --> 00:29:21.011
Bring me a signature and a check.

437
00:29:24.556 --> 00:29:25.641
Cheer up.

438
00:29:25.724 --> 00:29:27.935
Someone might throw a shoe at you.

439
00:29:28.936 --> 00:29:31.313
And you. get your hands
off my liquor and yourself

440
00:29:31.396 --> 00:29:33.315
down to the Angel's Flight
in the morning.

441
00:29:33.398 --> 00:29:35.150
Be my eyes. son.

442
00:29:35.734 --> 00:29:37.027
Time and a half.

443
00:29:37.110 --> 00:29:39.071
- It's New Year's Eve.
- Earn it.

444
00:30:17.025 --> 00:30:18.527
Very good. <i>papi.</i>

445
00:30:23.365 --> 00:30:25.033
I think she's jealous of me.

446
00:30:30.539 --> 00:30:34.001
Did you bring some more of that tequila?

447
00:30:34.084 --> 00:30:35.460
It's called mescal.

448
00:30:35.544 --> 00:30:37.546
And if you want some.
you better get it yourself.

449
00:30:37.629 --> 00:30:39.131
I ain't your fucking help.

450
00:30:48.223 --> 00:30:50.767
Either take them off
or put them back on. <i>papi.</i>

451
00:30:50.851 --> 00:30:52.019
Make up your mind.

452
00:30:52.102 --> 00:30:53.895
What are you in a rush for?

453
00:30:53.979 --> 00:30:56.606
- I need sleep.
- Sleep here.

454
00:30:56.690 --> 00:30:58.483
I sleep in my own bed.

455
00:31:01.820 --> 00:31:03.780
I'll give you 6.000 for this dump.

456
00:31:03.989 --> 00:31:07.075
Ha. ha! Six thousand
and she won't even sleep here.

457
00:31:07.868 --> 00:31:09.286
It's a fair price.

458
00:31:09.369 --> 00:31:10.787
It's a price.

459
00:31:10.871 --> 00:31:12.789
It's a great fucking price.

460
00:31:12.873 --> 00:31:14.499
You don't even have citrus.

461
00:31:14.583 --> 00:31:16.168
You know I'm working this one.

462
00:31:16.251 --> 00:31:17.544
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

463
00:31:22.674 --> 00:31:24.092
It's a big case.

464
00:31:24.176 --> 00:31:26.094
You don't usually do the bigs.

465
00:31:27.054 --> 00:31:28.263
I'm doing this one.

466
00:31:30.640 --> 00:31:33.143
Six thousand five hundred.

467
00:31:34.436 --> 00:31:36.104
Enjoy your bed.

468
00:31:36.188 --> 00:31:37.272
I will.

469
00:31:49.076 --> 00:31:51.787
<i>And right there.
in that very window.</i>

470
00:31:52.788 --> 00:31:54.790
sat the boy's parents.

471
00:31:54.873 --> 00:31:58.376
Watching. hoping. tragically unaware...

472
00:31:58.460 --> 00:32:03.215
...that their tiny innocent
was already ascending to heaven

473
00:32:03.298 --> 00:32:07.135
in the clutches of this demon.

474
00:32:07.219 --> 00:32:09.930
This instrument of death.

475
00:32:11.014 --> 00:32:13.100
Thank you. ma'am.
Happy New Year. sir.

476
00:32:13.183 --> 00:32:16.353
Happy New Year!
Horror at Angel's Flight.

477
00:32:16.436 --> 00:32:18.688
baby murdered.
read all about it.

478
00:33:43.815 --> 00:33:45.358
Looking for something?

479
00:33:46.234 --> 00:33:47.819
Close the blinds. Steve.

480
00:33:48.278 --> 00:33:51.239
Maybe I couldn't see him so good
and shot him by accident.

481
00:33:51.323 --> 00:33:54.784
Look. fellas. if I... interrupted

482
00:33:54.868 --> 00:33:57.996
some sort of tender moment.
I sincerely apologize.

483
00:33:58.079 --> 00:33:59.164
Guy's a laugh riot.

484
00:33:59.247 --> 00:34:00.790
Take it easy with that thing.

485
00:34:01.499 --> 00:34:03.501
What the hell
are you doing here. Mason?

486
00:34:03.585 --> 00:34:05.211
You gotta know something stinks
around Dodson

487
00:34:05.212 --> 00:34:06.504
or else you wouldn't be here.

488
00:34:06.588 --> 00:34:08.547
Get paid to look into things.
That's what I'm doing.

489
00:34:08.548 --> 00:34:10.592
Hell with this. We got him on a B&E.

490
00:34:10.675 --> 00:34:12.092
Let's run him in. torch his license.

491
00:34:12.093 --> 00:34:14.054
- Get the fuck off me.
- Settle down.

492
00:34:14.137 --> 00:34:15.889
Ease up. God damn it.

493
00:34:20.602 --> 00:34:22.437
You got something
says Dodson's clean.

494
00:34:22.520 --> 00:34:24.564
you'll be doing him a favor
by letting us know.

495
00:34:26.775 --> 00:34:30.445
...tiny innocent
was already ascending to heaven.

496
00:34:32.864 --> 00:34:35.158
Right after the Dodsons
found little Charlie dead.

497
00:34:35.242 --> 00:34:36.867
a green phaeton goes
tearing up Hill Street.

498
00:34:36.868 --> 00:34:38.203
clipped the trolley.

499
00:34:38.286 --> 00:34:40.455
You think
that's our kidnapper?

500
00:34:40.538 --> 00:34:42.290
Where did you get this phaeton shit?

501
00:34:42.374 --> 00:34:44.167
Traffic cop working
the bottom of the flight.

502
00:34:44.251 --> 00:34:45.751
He didn't think anything of it
at the time

503
00:34:45.752 --> 00:34:46.962
because most cops are stupid.

504
00:34:49.047 --> 00:34:50.257
Go check it out.

505
00:35:02.310 --> 00:35:04.396
Your ape almost broke my camera.

506
00:35:04.479 --> 00:35:06.481
My ape would've broke your jaw.

507
00:35:06.564 --> 00:35:07.857
- Here.
- What's that?

508
00:35:07.941 --> 00:35:09.442
For the car thing.

509
00:35:09.526 --> 00:35:11.319
Save it
for a better sketch artist.

510
00:35:11.403 --> 00:35:13.446
Man in hat? That sure narrows it down.

511
00:35:13.530 --> 00:35:16.574
What about the guy on the phone
or the one in the car?

512
00:35:16.658 --> 00:35:18.159
Halfway to Rio is my guess.

513
00:35:18.243 --> 00:35:19.828
Is that why you like Dodson for it?

514
00:35:19.911 --> 00:35:21.371
Got to arrest somebody.

